<seg id="12">Summary</seg>
<seg id="13">In 2005 and 2006, the two Supreme Audit Institutions of the Federal Republic of Germany and the Czech Republic, the Federal Audit Office (BRH) and the Nejvyšší kontrolní úřad (Nkú), carried out parallel audits of expenditure on the construction of the Prague – Dresden motorway (D 8 motorway in the Czech Republic and a 17 motorway in the Federal Republic of Germany).</seg>
<seg id="14">The two highways are connected by a border bridge jointly financed by both states.</seg>
<seg id="15">The cooperation with the NKÚ enabled the BRH to carry out an in-depth examination of the cost-effectiveness of the use of funds in the construction of the border bridge.</seg>
<seg id="16">In the course of its cooperation with the BRH, the NKÚ received data from German bridges and tunnels for its own cost comparisons.</seg>
