<seg id="850">Therefore, the Czech taxpayers should not have reported the electricity deliveries in their ZM for 2005.</seg>
<seg id="851">The fact that both taxpayers treated the supply of electrical energy in their ZM as intra-community supplies led to a difference in the amount of CZK 503,881,939 in MIAS.</seg>
<seg id="852">Final remark</seg>
<seg id="853">Through the cooperation, the goals of the BRH and the NKÚ were achieved.</seg>
<seg id="854">Both audit offices gained in-depth knowledge of VAT management systems in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="855">The cooperation revealed differences in the two systems and in the legal regulations governing VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="856">During the parallel tests, interesting cases of intra-community deliveries or acquisitions came to light.</seg>
<seg id="857">Some of them are worth further observation.</seg>
<seg id="858">On the basis of the audit results, both audit courts developed recommendations for the management of VAT.</seg>
<seg id="859">The follow-up of these recommendations in the form of a control audit should be part of the further observation.</seg>
<seg id="860">The new experience and knowledge gained through the cooperation of the two accounting courts are the basis for the successful execution of future audits in the field of VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="861">Communiqué</seg>
<seg id="862">This report was drawn up in Czech, English and German and signed by the president of the Supreme Audit Office of the Czech Republic and the president of the Federal Audit Court of the Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
