<seg id="604">The examination and evaluation of the offers is a particularly vulnerable phase of the award procedure.</seg>
<seg id="605">For example, bidders may be unfairly excluded or offers that do not meet the requirements may be left in competition.</seg>
<seg id="606">Due to the preference or disadvantage of bidders, the result of the evaluation can be impermissibly impaired and thus the determination of the economically most advantageous offer can be prevented.</seg>
<seg id="607">The awarding authority must therefore take special precautions to ensure that the persons responsible for the examination and evaluation meet the requirements for integrity and expertise.</seg>
<seg id="608">It must also ensure the transparency and traceability of the procedure and the decisions taken.</seg>
