<seg id="695">Summary Findings</seg>
<seg id="696">The regulations for the examination and evaluation of the offers comply with the requirements of the EU in both countries.</seg>
<seg id="697">However, the respective regulations differ with regard to details of the procedure and the selection of the persons involved.</seg>
<seg id="698">In Germany, the procedure is more regulated than in the Czech Republic by detailed requirements, in particular for the implementation of the multi-eyes principle and for the protection of offers.</seg>
<seg id="699">The same applies to the specifications on the basis of which the appropriateness of the prices offered is to be checked.</seg>
<seg id="700">In both countries, some of the procurement procedures examined had to be found to be insufficient or not sufficiently documented for essential procedural steps in the examination and evaluation of tenders.</seg>
<seg id="701">However, possible manipulative interventions are favoured without comprehensibility and transparency of the examination and evaluation decisions.</seg>
<seg id="702">A particularly serious defect was the handing over of all offers to third parties without the contracting authority having sufficiently looked through and documented the offers beforehand and thus protected them from possible manipulation in the further procedure.</seg>
<seg id="703">If contracting authorities have tasks carried out by third parties during the examination and evaluation of the offers, sufficient precautions and an increased inspection effort are required in order to counter the increased risk of manipulation.</seg>
<seg id="704">When assessing the appropriateness of prices, the audited services in Germany did not always make full use of the specified instruments and did not adequately examine the price structure of the offers.</seg>
<seg id="705">In the Czech Republic, complaints arose above all in the aptitude test and in the application of the evaluation criteria.</seg>
<seg id="706">Conclusion of the procurement procedure</seg>
<seg id="707">After the examination and evaluation of the offers, the award procedure is concluded by granting the award or by cancelling the procedure.</seg>
<seg id="708">Requirements of EU law and Prevention of corruption</seg>
