<seg id="571">II. incorrect surplus result (e.g. relocation/postponement of a matter not to be objected to under VAT law to another tax period)</seg>
<seg id="572">III. Cash effectivity (payment of the set more income)</seg>
<seg id="573">CZ:</seg>
<seg id="574">The Czech Tax Administration monitors the number of tax audits carried out, the amount of tax surplus broken down by type of tax, the number of audited taxpayers and the number of audited tax periods.</seg>
<seg id="575">Other tax procedures (on-site investigations, Dunning procedures) are monitored in the same way.</seg>
<seg id="576">Regardless of this, the amount of additional payments and incoming payments are recorded.</seg>
<seg id="577">Statistics on tax liabilities are broken down by type of tax. However, there is no distinction between tax debts incurred as a result of a tax return and those arising from audit procedures of the FA.</seg>
<seg id="578">Germany: no, the statistics compiled at federal level for auditors and VAT special auditors do not distinguish according to the above criteria.</seg>
<seg id="579">Most tax authorities, where local surveys were carried out, did not differentiate in this respect either.</seg>
<seg id="580">* Are Exam fields with results recorded?</seg>
<seg id="581">CZ: yes, the FA can select examination cases on the basis of criteria linked to selected indicators stored in the ATIS System.</seg>
<seg id="582">Germany: There are no regulations at the Federal level.</seg>
<seg id="583">Accordingly, the statistics compiled at federal level for auditors and VAT special auditors do not provide such information.</seg>
<seg id="584">However, the federal and state finance ministries have agreed on a common approach.</seg>
<seg id="585">Accordingly, auditors and tax investigators of the Länder have to enter the additional tax result they have achieved when a certain threshold value is exceeded in ZAUBER.</seg>
<seg id="586">In this case, additional information must be provided, e.g. on the origin of the VAT surplus.</seg>
<seg id="587">* Which are the most common findings?</seg>
<seg id="588">CZ:</seg>
<seg id="589">- Large taxable companies have unjustifiably claimed input tax deduction for purchased supplies and services,</seg>
<seg id="590">* which were not used for an entrepreneurial activity according to § 72 (1) CZ UStG;</seg>
<seg id="591">* which were used for representation expenses in accordance with § 75 (3) CZ UStG;</seg>
<seg id="592">* due to invoices that do not comply with the requirements of § 73 (1) CZ UStG</seg>
<seg id="593">- large companies subject to tax have failed to register the VAT to be paid as provided for in § 21 (1) CZ UStG.</seg>
<seg id="594">Germany: There are no regulations at the Federal level.</seg>
<seg id="595">Accordingly, the statistics compiled at federal level for auditors and VAT special auditors do not provide such information.</seg>
<seg id="596">Findings on VAT from audits of large companies are not recorded separately by the countries.</seg>
<seg id="597">However, the federal Central Tax Office can evaluate the ZAUBER database, in which auditors and tax investigators of the Länder have to enter the additional tax result they have achieved if a certain threshold is exceeded.</seg>
<seg id="598">* Does the financial administration analyse audit fields with significant results and draw conclusions for Strategic Management?</seg>
<seg id="599">CZ: yes, for example, nationwide inspections are carried out with regard to risky goods and industries.</seg>
<seg id="600">Germany: There are no regulations at the Federal level.</seg>
<seg id="601">Accordingly, the statistics compiled at federal level for auditors and VAT special auditors do not provide any information about particularly "productive" audit fields.</seg>
<seg id="602">With regard to the analysis of such information, the usefulness and the way in which it was further used, there were different views among the survey bodies.</seg>
<seg id="603">Some financial directorates provide such information to FAs, but FAs are free to use it or not.</seg>
<seg id="604">4.5.4 comparison and evaluation</seg>
<seg id="605">As a result, large amounts of information are processed automatically in the CZ. Among other things, data from VAT audits, as well as key figures from balance sheets, profit and loss accounts are processed in the System.</seg>
<seg id="606">CZ is able to control the selection of high-risk cases based on a wide range of information.</seg>
<seg id="607">The same applies to the evaluation and Management of VAT audits in general.</seg>
<seg id="608">In the Czech Republic, the establishment of a special tax office for large enterprises is planned for 2012.</seg>
<seg id="609">In Germany, the financial administration does not collect comparable amounts of data.</seg>
<seg id="610">Accordingly, it is more difficult to fulfill these tasks in the same way.</seg>
<seg id="611">The emphasis is more on the selection of relevant individual cases.</seg>
